                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Arrr, ahoy matey! Tell this old sea-dog yer city or ZIP code — and whether ye be headin' to work, hittin' the shops, or chasin' adventures outside — an' I'll chart the best garb fer the day. Savvy?\n\nIf ye want quick general tips while ye fetch that:\n- Warm / sunny (70°F+/21°C+): light cotton shirt, shorts or light pants, sun hat & shades. SPF, aye.\n- Mild / breezy (50–70°F / 10–21°C): layers — a tee with a light jacket or cardigan; long pants.\n- Cool / chilly (32–50°F / 0–10°C): sweater, medium jacket, closed shoes; consider a scarf.\n- Cold / freezing (<32°F / 0°C): heavy coat, hat, gloves, insulated boots; layers beneath.\n- Rainy: waterproof jacket or poncho, water-resistant shoes, umbrella.\n- Windy: windbreaker and tight hat so the gale don’t steal it.\n\nGive me yer location and plans, an’ I’ll give ye a tailored outfit, Arr!",
